Sarah Silverman claimed she was paid less than her male friend for a gig at the New York Comedy Club . 
  The comic and feminist campaigner was trying to highlight the gender pay gap . 
  But club owner Al Martin revealed the story was false because her male counterpart Todd Barry was booked for the gig and was paid $60 instead of $10 . 
  Silverman has apologized and said she fabricated the story for a video . 
  She said the story should not be used to undermine the pay gap campaign . 
 